  <!-- Section 3: Database Schema Specifications -->
  <h1>3. Database Schema Specifications</h1>
  <p>
    The relational database schema is configured on **Supabase (PostgreSQL)**. Key constraints and foreign keys are set up with `ON DELETE CASCADE` or `ON DELETE SET NULL` behaviors to ensure data integrity during deletions.
  </p>

  <h2>A. Table: profiles</h2>
  <p>Stores identity and system privileges for all user categories.</p>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Column Name</th>
        <th>Data Type</th>
        <th>Constraints</th>
        <th>Description</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>id</td>
        <td>UUID</td>
        <td>Primary Key (References auth.users)</td>
        <td>Unique User Auth ID.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>full_name</td>
        <td>Text</td>
        <td>Not Null</td>
        <td>User's first and last name.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>email</td>
        <td>Text</td>
        <td>Not Null, Unique</td>
        <td>Registered email address.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>role</td>
        <td>Text</td>
        <td>Not Null</td>
        <td>Privilege level: student, mentor, employee, admin.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>area</td>
        <td>Text</td>
        <td>Nullable</td>
        <td>Assigned operational location (e.g. Talcher, Ib Valley).</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>signature_data</td>
        <td>Text</td>
        <td>Nullable</td>
        <td>Base64 PNG string representing the hand-drawn signature.</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>B. Table: applications</h2>
  <p>Maintains Letter of Recommendation (LOR) registrations submitted by employees.</p>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Column Name</th>
        <th>Data Type</th>
        <th>Constraints</th>
        <th>Description</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>id</td>
        <td>UUID</td>
        <td>Primary Key</td>
        <td>Unique application ID.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>status</td>
        <td>Text</td>
        <td>Not Null</td>
        <td>Status: pending_hq, pending_area, approved, rejected.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>student_name</td>
        <td>Text</td>
        <td>Not Null</td>
        <td>Student's full name.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>student_email</td>
        <td>Text</td>
        <td>Not Null</td>
        <td>Contact email address.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>roll_no</td>
        <td>Text</td>
        <td>Nullable</td>
        <td>Student's university roll number.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>university</td>
        <td>Text</td>
        <td>Nullable</td>
        <td>Attending college or university.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>student_id</td>
        <td>UUID</td>
        <td>References profiles(id) ON DELETE SET NULL</td>
        <td>Links the LOR to the registered student user account.</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>C. Table: internships</h2>
  <p>Defines active student training configurations, guidance mentors, and serial numbers.</p>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Column Name</th>
        <th>Data Type</th>
        <th>Constraints</th>
        <th>Description</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>id</td>
        <td>UUID</td>
        <td>Primary Key</td>
        <td>Unique internship record identifier.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>student_id</td>
        <td>UUID</td>
        <td>References profiles(id) ON DELETE CASCADE</td>
        <td>Linked student user.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>mentor_id</td>
        <td>UUID</td>
        <td>References profiles(id) ON DELETE SET NULL</td>
        <td>Assigned guiding mentor.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>serial_no</td>
        <td>Text</td>
        <td>Unique, Not Null</td>
        <td>Auto-incrementing serial string used for certificate registry.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>start_date</td>
        <td>Date</td>
        <td>Not Null</td>
        <td>Joining date.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>end_date</td>
        <td>Date</td>
        <td>Not Null</td>
        <td>Completion date.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>certificate_url</td>
        <td>Text</td>
        <td>Nullable</td>
        <td>Signed link to issued certificate PDF.</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <!-- Section 4: Security Policies -->
  <h1>4. Security & Access Control Policies</h1>
  <p>
    The portal is built around a secure architecture designed to protect sensitive data and prevent unauthorized operations.
  </p>

  <h2>A. Row-Level Security (RLS) Policies</h2>
  <p>
    RLS is enabled on all tables in PostgreSQL. When a client performs a select, insert, or update query, the database engine verifies the user's role and session ID.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Profiles:</strong> Authenticated users can read profiles, but users can only edit their own profile details.</li>
    <li><strong>Attendance/Logbooks/Leaves:</strong> Students can only view and manage records tied to their own internship_id. Mentors can view and edit records for internships where mentor_id = auth.uid().</li>
    <li><strong>Administrators:</strong> Global and Area Admins have a wildcard override policy allowing full read/write access.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>B. Next.js Routing Middleware (RBAC)</h2>
  <p>
    A centralized middleware runs on every route request. It intercepts the user's session JWT token, decodes their role, and verifies they have permission to access the requested page, preventing URL manipulation attacks.
  </p>

  <h2>C. Cryptographic Signature Safeguard</h2>
  <p>
    Signatures for Mentors and Area Training Officers are drawn via canvas vectors and saved in the database as base64 strings in RLS-protected tables. 
    The system does not store signatures in a public file folder. They are drawn directly from the database memory into the PDF during generation and are never exposed as independent URLs, preventing students from accessing or copying the raw signatures.
  </p>

